M|Comp|tx|\| Factor \| Self-Implementation \| EOS Implementer \|
M|Comp|tx|\|--------\|-------------------\|-----------------\|
M|Comp|tx|\| **Cost** \| Free (book + time) \| $50K-$100K+ over 2 years \|
M|Comp|tx|\| **Speed** \| Slower (learning while doing) \| Faster (experienced facilitator) \|
M|Comp|tx|\| **Facilitation** \| Integrator or Visionary facilitates (hard to participate and facilitate) \| Neutral third party facilitates (leadership fully participates) \|
M|Comp|tx|\| **Accountability** \| Self-policed \| External accountability partner \|
M|Comp|tx|\| **Customization** \| hi flexibility (can adapt tools) \| Purist approach (tools used as designed) \|
M|Comp|tx|\| **Common for** \| Bootstrapped companies, strong Integrators \| Funded companies, teams w/ internal conflict \|
M|Comp|tx|\| **Risk** \| Higher (easy to skip hard parts) \| Lower (Implementer pushes through resistance) \|
M|When|it|The leadership team has read *Traction* and is aligned on implementing EOS
M|When|it|The Integrator is a strong facilitator who can run sn
M|When|it|Budget constraints make an Implementer impractical
M|When|it|The company is smaller (under 20 people) and the dynamics are simpler
M|When|it|The leadership team has unresolved conflict that requires a neutral party
M|When|it|No one on the team is a strong enough facilitator
M|When|it|Previous self-implementation attempts have stalled
M|When|it|The company is growing fast and cannot afford a slow rollout
M|When|it|The budget allows for the investment ($4K-$8K per sn, typically 10-12 sn)
M|Gett|tx|EOS only works if the entire leadership team is committed. Partial adoption creates more problems than it solves.
M|The |**St|Share the book.** Give every leadership team member a cp of *Traction*. Ask them to read it within two weeks.
M|The |**St|Discuss openly.** Schedule a 2-hour meeting to discuss:
M|The |it|What resonated? What did not?
M|The |it|What problems cld EOS solve for us?
M|The |it|What concerns or objections do people have?
M|The |**St|Address objections honestly.**
M|The |tx|\| Common Objection \| rp \|
M|The |tx|\|-----------------\|----------\|
M|The |tx|\| "We don't have time for another meeting" \| Level 10 replaces your existing meetings, not adds to them. Most companies cut total meeting time. \|
M|The |tx|\| "This is too rigid" \| The tools are simple and flexible. The discipline is what creates results. \|
M|The |tx|\| "We've tried frameworks before" \| EOS is not a flavor-of-the-month. It is a complete operating sy adopted consistently for two years. \|
M|The |tx|\| "I don't want to be told how to run my department" \| EOS defines what to achieve, not how to achieve it. Your autonomy within your seat is preserved. \|
M|The |tx|\| "Our business is different" \| EOS works for every entrepreneurial company. Over 250,000 companies use it across every industry. \|
M|The |**St|Commitment vote.** After the discussion, ask each leader: "Are you in? Yes or no." Anything less than full commitment from the entire leadership team means EOS will struggle.
M|Roll|tx|Once the leadership team has done Focus Day, VB1, and VB2, it is time to share the vision w/ the entire company.
M|The |**Du|** 90 minutes
M|The |**At|** Everyone in the company
M|The |**Ag|**
M|The |tx|1. **What is EOS?** (10 min) Brief overview of the Six Key cp
M|The |tx|2. **Our Core Values** (15 min) Share each value w/ behavioral indicators and examples
M|The |tx|3. **Our Core Focus** (10 min) Purpose and niche
M|The |4. *|10-Year Target, 3-Year Picture, 1-Year Plan, Quarterly Rocks
M|The |tx|5. **What Changes for You** (15 min) Level 10 meetings at every level, rocks for every team, scorecards for every department
M|The |tx|6. **Q&A** (20 min) Open floor for questions
M|Depa|Afte|
M|Depa|it|[ ] Share how the department supports the company rocks
M|Depa|it|[ ] Set department-level rocks for the quarter
M|Depa|it|[ ] bd a department-level Scorecard
M|Depa|it|[ ] Schedule the department's weekly Level 10 meeting
M|Depa|it|[ ] Answer team-specific questions
M|Comm|tx|\| fl \| Root Cause \| Prevention \|
M|Comm|tx|\|---------\|-----------\|------------\|
M|Comm|tx|\| **EOS fades after 3 months** \| Leadership loses discipline when initial excitement wears off \| Commit to the full 2-year journey. Schedule all sn in advance. \|
M|Comm|| **|the meeting happens every week, no exceptions. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Visionary disengages** \| Visionaries get bored w/ operational discipline \| Define the Visionary's specific roles and keep them engaged in st IDS. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Integrator overwhelmed** \| Integrator tries to do everything \| Delegate operational functions. The Integrator manages leaders, not tasks. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Rocks are set but not tracked** \| Weekly rv skipped or superficial \| Track rocks in every Level 10. IDS off-track rocks immediately. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **People issues avoided** \| Leadership avoids hard conversations \| Use the People Analyzer as an objective tool. Set 90-day deadlines. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Core values are ignored** \| Values defined but not used in hiring, firing, or reviews \| Reference values in every people decision. Fire someone who violates values (it sends a message). \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Partial adoption** \| Some leaders do EOS, others do not \| Full leadership team must be committed. No opt-outs. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Overcomplication** \| Adding extra tools, extra metrics, extra meetings \| Keep it simple. EOS is powerful bc it is simple. Resist the urge to add complexity. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **No cascading to departments** \| EOS stays at the leadership level \| Every department shd have Level 10s, rocks, and scorecards within 6 months. \|
M|EOS |tx|Use this assessment quarterly to track your EOS implementation progress. Rate each item 1-5 (1 = not started, 5 = mastered).
M|EOS |tx|Rate each item 1-5 (1 = not started, 5 = mastered). 30 items total across all six cp.
M|EOS |tx|\| cp \| Key Items to Rate \|
M|EOS |tx|\|-----------\|------------------\|
M|EOS |tx|\| **Vision** \| V/TO complete, leadership aligned, shared w/ org, reviewed quarterly, filters all decisions \|
M|EOS |tx|\| **People** \| Accountability Chart defined, single owners, People Analyzer run, GWC assessed, tough decisions made in 90 days \|
M|EOS |tx|\| **Data** \| 5-15 weekly metrics, owners and goals set, reviewed in Level 10, off-track IDS'd, department scorecards exist \|
M|EOS |tx|\| **Issues** \| IDS used consistently, root cause focus, permanent solutions, both lists maintained, safe to raise issues \|
M|EOS |tx|\| **Process** \| 5-7 core processes identified, documented, trained and followed, compliance measured, reviewed quarterly \|
M|EOS |tx|\| **Traction** \| Rocks set and tracked, 80%+ completion, weekly Level 10s, meetings score 8+, to-do completion 90%+ \|
M|EOS |**Sc|**
M|EOS |- **|** EOS mastery. Fully embedded.
M|EOS |- **|** Strong adoption. Close remaining gaps.
M|EOS |- **|** Good progress. Focus on lowest-scoring areas.
M|EOS |- **|** Early implementation. Stay the course.
M|EOS |- **|** Just starting. Commit to the two-year journey.